# .cursorrules

# SIGS Design Agent Game Demo — Cursor AI Rules

> Version: 2.0.0 | Updated: 2026-04-23
>
# These rules guide Cursor AI when working with this codebase.

# --------------------------------------------------
# PROJECT OVERVIEW
# --------------------------------------------------

Project: SIGS Design Agent Game Demo — AR-enabled campus exploration platform
Tech Stack: Python/FastAPI backend, native HTML/CSS/JS frontend, PostgreSQL cloud DB
Package Manager: uv (Python), npm (frontend)
Linting: Ruff (backend)

# --------------------------------------------------
# CODE STYLING RULES
# --------------------------------------------------

# Python
- Use snake_case for files, variables, functions
- Use PascalCase for classes
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- Maximum function length: 200 lines
- Maximum file length: 800 lines
- Use docstrings for function/class documentation
- No bare except clauses — always specify exception type

# JavaScript
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- Use kebab-case for file names and CSS classes
- Use JSDoc style comments for functions

# SQL
- Use parameterized queries ONLY
- Never concatenate strings for SQL queries

# --------------------------------------------------
# NAMING CONVENTIONS
# --------------------------------------------------

# API endpoints: /api/v1/ + plural lowercase nouns
# Examples: /api/v1/users, /api/v1/designs, /api/v1/sessions

# File naming:
# Python: user_service.py, database/connection.py
# HTML/CSS/JS: game-board.html, api-client.js
# Tests: test_<module_name>.py (mirrors source path)

# --------------------------------------------------
# TESTING RULES
# --------------------------------------------------

# One test file per source file
# Test paths mirror source paths:
# backend/database/serve.py → test/backend/database/test_serve.py
# backend/api/design.py → test/backend/api/test_design.py

# Use pytest for testing
# Use pytest-asyncio for async tests
# Use httpx for HTTP client testing

# --------------------------------------------------
# API CONVENTIONS
# --------------------------------------------------

# RESTful API with JSON responses
# Prefix all API routes with /api/v1/

# Unified response format:
# Success: {"code": 0, "message": "success", "data": {...}}
# Error: {"code": 40001, "message": "error description", "data": null}

# Error codes:
# 0 = success
# 40001 = bad parameters
# 40101 = auth failed (API Key missing or invalid)
# 40401 = resource not found
# 50001 = server error

# Authentication: X-API-Key header

# --------------------------------------------------
# GIT COMMIT RULES
# --------------------------------------------------

# Commit format: <type>: <description>
# Types: feat, fix, refactor, test, docs, style, chore
# Examples: "feat: add user registration endpoint"

# Branches:
# main = development branch
# serve = stable/production branch
# feature/xxx = optional feature branches

# --------------------------------------------------
# SECURITY RULES
# --------------------------------------------------

# ALL external input must be validated
# NEVER hardcode secrets (API keys, passwords)
# Use environment variables for sensitive data
# Never log sensitive information
# Never expose internal details in error responses

# Required environment variables:
# DATABASE_URL, DATABASE_NAME, API_KEY, API_HOST, API_PORT, FRONTEND_URL

# --------------------------------------------------
# DOCUMENTATION RULES
# --------------------------------------------------

# When asked to write a document:
# 1. Read doc/00_文档存放规则.md first
# 2. Determine document type to choose correct directory
# 3. Use naming format: [description]_[YYYY-MM-DD].md (for reports and plans)
# 4. Include standard header metadata
# 5. Update doc/INDEX.md with new document link

# Document directories:
# doc/01_architecture/ = technical architecture, system design
# doc/02_product/ = interaction design, feature requirements
# doc/03_reports/ = code reports, audits, reviews
# doc/04_plans/ = work plans, roadmaps, todos
# doc/05_meetings/ = meeting notes, decisions
# doc/06_references/ = reference materials
# doc/archive/ = archived documents

# --------------------------------------------------
# COMMON COMMANDS
# --------------------------------------------------

# Backend setup:
# cd backend && uv sync

# Run dev server:
# cd backend && uv run uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload

# Code linting:
# ruff check .
# ruff check --fix .
# ruff format .

# Run tests:
# pytest

# --------------------------------------------------
# CODE QUALITY CHECKLIST
# --------------------------------------------------

# Before considering a task complete:
# - [ ] Code follows naming conventions
# - [ ] Functions ≤ 200 lines, files ≤ 800 lines
# - [ ] No bare except clauses
# - [ ] SQL uses parameterized queries
# - [ ] Secrets via environment variables only
# - [ ] Test file created (mirrors source path)
# - [ ] Passes ruff check .
# - [ ] If document created, follows doc/00_文档存放规则.md

# --------------------------------------------------
# AUTHORITATIVE RULES
# --------------------------------------------------

# When rules conflict, follow this priority:
# 1. 开发规则.md (highest priority)
# 2. AGENT.md
# 3. This file (.cursorrules)
# 4. Other documentation

# Always read 开发规则.md for the most authoritative rules.
